---
import AppLayout from "../../../layouts/AppLayout.astro";
---

<AppLayout
  title="Grimora Legal And Attributions"
  description="Legal notices and source attributions for Grimora, an unofficial Magic: The Gathering utility."
  currentPath="/apps/grimora/legal"
>
  <article class="contentPage">
    <header class="contentPageHeader">
      <p class="eyebrow">Grimora</p>
      <h1>Legal And Attributions</h1>
      <p class="contentIntro">
        Grimora is a free unofficial Magic: The Gathering utility. These notes
        describe the data sources and rights notices that apply to the app.
      </p>
      <p class="lastUpdated">Last updated: May 20, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>Unofficial Fan Content</h2>
      <p>
        Grimora is unofficial Fan Content permitted under the Fan Content
        Policy. Not approved/endorsed by Wizards. Portions of the materials
        used are property of Wizards of the Coast. &copy; Wizards of the Coast
        LLC.
      </p>
      <p>
        Grimora is not affiliated with, produced by, approved by, endorsed by,
        or sponsored by Wizards of the Coast, Scryfall, MTGJSON, or Apple.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>Scryfall</h2>
      <p>
        Grimora uses Scryfall as a source for Magic: The Gathering card data and
        card imagery. Card images, card text, mana symbols, expansion symbols,
        and related Magic materials are owned by Wizards of the Coast or their
        respective owners.
      </p>
      <p>
        Grimora uses local and bulk-style data where possible and should avoid
        excessive live requests to Scryfall services.
      </p>
      <div class="linkPanel">
        <p>Scryfall resources:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://scryfall.com/docs/api">Scryfall API docs</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://scryfall.com/docs/api/images">Scryfall card imagery docs</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://scryfall.com/docs/api/rate-limits">Scryfall rate limits</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://scryfall.com/docs/terms">Scryfall terms</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>MTGJSON</h2>
      <p>
        Grimora uses MTGJSON as a source for Magic: The Gathering data and price
        information. MTGJSON publishes its MIT-style project license on its
        license page.
      </p>
      <div class="linkPanel">
        <p>MTGJSON resource:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://mtgjson.com/license/">MTGJSON license</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>Wizards of the Coast</h2>
      <p>
        Magic: The Gathering and related intellectual property are owned by
        Wizards of the Coast. Grimora follows the public fan-content guidance
        published by Wizards.
      </p>
      <div class="linkPanel">
        <p>Wizards resource:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://company.wizards.com/en/legal/fancontentpolicy">Wizards Fan Content Policy</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contentSection">
      <h2>Apple Metadata References</h2>
      <p>
        Grimora's website pages provide the public privacy, support, and
        marketing URLs required for App Store Connect metadata.
      </p>
      <div class="linkPanel">
        <p>Apple resources:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://developer.apple.com/help/app-store-connect/reference/app-privacy/">Apple App Privacy reference</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://developer.apple.com/help/app-store-connect/reference/app-information/">App Store Connect app information reference</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</AppLayout>
